Judge George O'Toole told jurors in the Boston Marathon bombing case they are not to attend this year's race or related events . 
 The race takes place next Monday, April 20, and marks two years since Dzhokhar Tsarnaev and his brother planted two bombs at the finish line . 
 This as the the sentencing phase of the trial, in which witnesses will again be called to the stand, is expected begin next week and to take four weeks . 
 Tsarnaev faces either life in prison or the death penalty . 
 